1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:05,000
StellarFund — cross-border crowdfunding on Stellar, with USDC milestone escrow.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
First, connect a Stellar wallet — Freighter, Albedo, xBull, Lobstr and more.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
One click links your wallet to the app on Stellar Testnet.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
New here? Tap "Get Test USDC" for one-tap onboarding.

5
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:27,000
It funds the account, adds the USDC trustline, and mints 500 test USDC.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:33,000
No faucets to hunt for — you're ready to back a campaign in seconds.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Browse live campaigns across categories — Education, Health, Technology and more.

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Search and category filters make it easy to find a cause to support.

9
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Each campaign shows its goal, its progress, and its milestone schedule.

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Open a campaign to see the milestone timeline and how funds are released.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Contribute USDC — the amount is capped at the remaining goal.

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Funds are held in a smart-contract escrow, not by any middleman.

13
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Now let's create a brand-new campaign, live.

14
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Give it an identity: title, description, category, cover image and creator name.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Set the funding goal in USDC.

16
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Then define the milestones — each releases a tranche of funds as it's met.

17
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The milestones must sum to the goal; this is enforced on-chain.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Submitting deploys a dedicated escrow contract through the Factory.

19
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:02,000
The Factory creates and registers the campaign contract on Stellar Testnet.

20
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Sign the transaction in your wallet to confirm.

21
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:20,000
In a few seconds, the campaign is live on-chain.

22
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:24,000
No server holds the money — the contract does.

23
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Here's the campaign we just created, now appearing in the list.

24
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Its contract address is real and verifiable on stellar.expert.

25
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Proof that creation actually hit the chain.

26
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:47,000
We collect user feedback through a simple Google Form.

27
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:53,000
The Feedback button is always one click away.

28
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Real feedback drives what we build next.

29
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:05,000
The Proof of Users board reads straight from the blockchain.

30
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:11,000
It lists every unique backer wallet, with amounts and transaction links.

31
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Transparent, on-chain evidence — no numbers we could fake.

32
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Finally, the fiat on/off ramp powered by a SEP-24 anchor.

33
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Pay fiat to receive USDC, or cash out USDC back to fiat.

34
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:37,000
SEP-10 auth and the SEP-24 interactive flow run against the test anchor.

35
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Bridging traditional money and Stellar.

36
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:44,000
StellarFund — global funding, milestone-enforced, on Stellar. Thanks for watching!
